			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/08/05/as-long-as.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/08/05/if-its-a.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“if it’s a witch hunt, there are an awful lot of people around the president who just happen to be wearing pointy hats” —<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/plum-line/wp/2017/08/04/the-russia-investigation-is-getting-serious-and-president-trump-is-feeling-the-heat/\">Paul Waldman</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-08-04T19:09:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/08/04/if-its-a.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/08/05/without-the-lies.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“without the lies there would be virtually nothing for Trump to say and nothing left of his presidency” —<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/right-turn/wp/2017/08/04/how-can-kelly-tell-trump-the-truth-when-his-entire-presidency-is-built-on-lies/\">Jennifer Rubin</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-08-04T19:05:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/08/04/without-the-lies.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/08/02/so-the-line.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“So the line from the Trump team is essentially that they were trying to collude with the Russian government to help their campaign, but the attempt was unsuccessful.” —<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/plum-line/wp/2017/08/01/president-trump-is-now-directly-implicated-in-trying-to-cover-up-the-russia-scandal/\">Paul Waldman</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-08-01T21:26:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/08/01/so-the-line.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/08/02/what-but-some.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“What but some profound sense of inadequacy could explain the neediness and the nastiness, the pout and the pettiness, the vanity and the vulgarity, the anger and the aggression?” —<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/01/opinion/goodbye-anthony-scaramucci.html?smprod=nytcore-ipad&amp;smid=nytcore-ipad-share\">Roger Cohen</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-08-01T20:16:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/08/01/what-but-some.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/08/02/and-so-that.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“And so, that unnerving silence in the face of an erratic executive branch is an abdication, and those in positions of leadership bear particular responsibility.” —<a href=\"http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2017/07/31/my-party-is-in-denial-about-donald-trump-215442\">Sen. Jeff Flake–R, AZ</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-08-01T19:00:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/08/01/and-so-that.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/07/30/the-lesson-that.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“the lesson that … conservatives appear to be teaching … is that power is more important than principle, … compromise is failure, and … that facts don’t matter.” —<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/grade-point/wp/2017/07/26/its-not-liberals-on-campus-crushing-republican-ideas-its-conservatives/\">Brian C. Rosenberg</a></p>\n",
